main event: A bright, glowing object was spotted in the sky over Ohio in September 1966.
interesting points: The object was seen by multiple observers in various locations including Dayton, Fairborn, Xenia, and other nearby areas.
The object was described as being greenish in color and moving silently.
The object appeared to be solid and sharply outlined, not like a bright star.
The object changed brightness and seemed to increase in brightness at times.
The object was estimated to be about 500-600 yards away and moving at an estimated speed of 200-250 mph.
sighted object: A bright, glowing, greenish object in the sky
witnesses: Multiple civilian observers in various locations
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
